  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global: Supporting Global Professionalization of Corrections Management Training in Line with International Human Rights Standards</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enable the INL Global Corrections Training Program to adopt a curriculum that aligns with international human rights and uses advanced adult learning methodologies to professionalize corrections management.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">INL professional trainers; Corrections officers from selected countries; penitentiary institutions from selected countries; penitentiary institutions from other countries with access to the Global Corrections Training Curriculum.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to enable the INL Global Corrections Training Program to sustainably advance the global professionalization of corrections management in line with international human rights standards and best practices.</narrative>
